The paper deals with complexity and proof complexity, which are central topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It specifically focuses on resolution, a popular proof system in proof complexity, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of Razborov's hardness condensation technique suggests a connection to circuit complexity (cs.CR), while the space lower bounds in [Ben-Sasson and Nordstrom '08] indicate a link to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's exploration of trade-offs in proof complexity may also relate to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as proof complexity has applications in automated theorem proving and other AI-related fields.
